Dear Members,
2023 was a year of
paradox. Notable
milestones were
attained, leaving
an indelible mark
on our collective
memory. India
surpassed China to
become the world’s
most populous
country, positioning
India favourably
in solidifying its
trajectory towards
becoming one of the
foremost economies
worldwide.
Growing together – today
and tomorrow
Amidst a challenging external
landscape, Your Company
remained perseverant on its growth
path, guided by its heartbeat
encapsulated in 5 P’s - purpose,
people, planet, partnerships,
and performance.
With a steadfast commitment to
‘Make in India’, spanning 112 years,
your Company announced its tenth
factory in Odisha, reaffirming the
significance of India as a market.
Strengthening this further, your
Company is poised to invest INR
5,800 crore between 2020 and
2025, to develop new capabilities
and expand existing ones with
strong focus on sustained
growth and innovation.
Your Company recently split
its shares to make them more
accessible to shareholders.
This move has been positively
received, leading to the number
of shareholders being doubled.
We aim to further enhance
engagement levels, contributing to
the development of strong equity
and goodwill for your Company.
The existing General License
Agreements (“GLAs”) with the
Société des Produits Nestlé S.A.,
Switzerland enables your Company
to access their intellectual property
rights (“IPRs”) such as a global
portfolio of brands, proprietary
technology, patents, and research
and development capabilities by
the global network of 23 Research
& Development (“R&D”) Centres
including state-of-the-art R&D
Centre in India at Manesar,
Haryana. The access to this array
of resources ensures gives us
strategic advantage and ensures
that we remain at the forefront of
innovation. We seek your support
in the renewal of the GLA.
Balancing growth and
profitability consistently
The underlying fundamentals
of your Company continue to
be strong. Robust growth was
sustained across all categories,
with India becoming the largest
market worldwide for MAGGI and
the second-largest market for
KITKAT. Your Company’s total sales
grew by over xx % on the back
of xx and xx growth, navigating a
dynamic market landscape. This
testifies that over the past eight
consecutive years, your Company
has consistently delivered on its
promises.
The Out-of-Home business
continued to accelerate rapidly
and became the fastest-growing
business of your Company in India.
E-commerce sustained its upward
trajectory, contributing to XX% of
sales. All key brands and product
groups contributed to consistent
growth, despite escalating food
inflation and volatile commodity
prices.
By combining the power of its
brands, meticulous planning, astute
implementation and outstanding
execution, by a diverse team of
employees, partners, suppliers,
distributors and retailers, your
Company delivered “Performance
with Pride’.

Investing in innovation as
an engine for growth
Innovation is a core strength of
your Company, this underscores
its commitment to continuously
introduce new and exciting
offerings tailored to the evolving
consumer needs.
Over the past seven years, your
Company recalibrated, redirected,
and rejuvenated its product
portfolio, by launching over XX
new products. A significant
portion of sales in 2023 was
attributed to innovative products.
This includes plant-based protein
options, science-led nutrition
solutions and millet-based
products that cater to
diverse dietary needs.
The plant-based market presents
a significant opportunity. It offers
relevant Indian-centric plant-
based products that seamlessly
integrate and resonate with the
Indian palate, providing enhanced
culinary experiences and
nutritionally improved choices.
2023 was the International Year of
Millets. Your company launched
a slew of millet-based products
and was conferred with the ‘Best
Industry- Product Innovation for
Mainstreaming Millets Award’.
Amongst others, MAGGI Korean
noodles was also launched.

Expanding and accelerating
RUrban thrust
Your Company remained steadfast
on its RUrban journey by creating
infrastructure, portfolio, feet on
the ground, and opportunities.
This resulted in a notable upswing
in sales and expanded our direct
coverage footprint, encompassing
over 196,000 villages—close to the
milestone of 200,000 villages.

generation shift

heterogenous team.
Women are growing steadily in

part of succession plans. Their
development plans are closely
tracked and supported across
all business units, factories,
and branches in a quest for a
more inclusive, equitable future.

Carving our path to progress
